  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">To improve the resilience of vulnerable families to drought in South East Haiti</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">A consortium partnership action based on a regional DRR strategy, focusing mainly on: 
(a) disaster risk reduction through the promotion of scientific and technical research based on vulnerability and its effects on the most vulnerable populations, in order to strengthen local capacities and thus better respond to future crises. 
(b) support for respect for fundamental rights (water, education, health, etc.); 
(c) support for the economic and social development of the country. 

The role of this consortium is to defend the rights of the elderly and their inclusion in emergency and development programmes. Specifically, HelpAge will run workshops with communities and local stakeholders on gathering information on drought, historical events, identifying the most exposed areas and the resources involved and ensure older people and their issues are represented at sectoral and technical processes.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Drought risk and crisis management is improved through a resource information system and its vulnerabilities in the targeted areas</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Local actors are strengthened on crisis prevention and response through contingency plans targeted at drought</narrative>
  </description>
